==English==
===adjective===
...low bono...
#{{category:law}}The practice of law or profession in a manner so as to be accessible to more people -- not for free ([[pro bono]]), but not making very much money overall.
Use in a sentence might be "Most of my work is low bono," or "I took this case low bono."
